```json
{
"application": "Sockeye",
"software": [
"Python 3",
"GNU Parallel",
"Sockeye"
],
"resources": {
"walltime": "20 minutes",
"nodes": 1,
"cpus": 10,
"memory": "32 GB",
"storage": "/scratch/ex-kdd-1/rt/kddlab_sockeye/"
}
}
```

This script uses the Sockeye machine translation toolkit. It utilizes Python 3 for running the `experiment_parser.py` script and GNU Parallel for parallel execution. The script runs on a single node with 10 CPUs and 32 GB of memory, requesting a maximum runtime of 20 minutes. The output and error logs are stored in `/scratch/ex-kdd-1/rt/kddlab_sockeye/`. The script utilizes a virtual environment named "testvenv" for managing dependencies.
